<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[812,1420,193,940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">
<emphasis box="[813,1420,714,738]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1114,714,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">Ecology and distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[1126,1366,714,738]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Bulbothrix" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ventricosa">
<emphasis box="[1126,1366,714,738]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">Bulbothrix ventricosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was
</emphasis>
recorded only in the Central Cordillera in 
<collectingRegion country="Colombia" name="Risaralda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423">Risaralda department</collectingRegion>
, at between 1500 and 
<quantity box="[1148,1226,781,805]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.725" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" unit="m" value="1725.0">1725 m</quantity>
a.s.l., but its presence is assumed for the rest of the Colombian Andean region (
<bibRefCitation author="Wolf JHD" box="[897,1015,848,873]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" pagination="928 - 960" refId="ref9503" refString="Wolf JHD (1993) Diversity patterns and biomass of epiphytic bryophytes and lichens along an altitudinal gradient in the Northern Andes. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 80 (4): 928 - 960. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2399938" type="journal article" year="1993">Wolf 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernal R &amp; Gradstein SR &amp; Celis M" box="[1029,1231,848,873]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" pagination="1" refId="ref7665" refString="Bernal R, Gradstein SR, Celis M (Eds) (2020) Catalogo de Plantas y Liquenes de Colombia. v. 1. 1. Universidad Nacional de Colombia. Dataset / checklist. https: // doi. org / 10.15472 / 7 avdhn" type="journal article" year="2020">Bernal et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In the SNSM it was found on bark in coffee crops in sub-Andean forest between 
<quantity box="[909,1049,916,940]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.575" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.55" pageId="2" pageNumber="1423" unit="m" value="1575.0" valueMax="1600.0" valueMin="1550.0">1550-1600 m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
